list.item:
Allen said he had informed LucRobert Luc, First Secretary of the French Embassy in the United Kingdom. of British proposal subsequent to his earlier conversation with US (Embtel 1529, March 20, repeated Paris 446, Vienna 72
Not printed; it reported the following three proposals as the basis for the British reply to the Austrian memorandum on occupation policy:
“a. Gradual elimination certain UK HICOM’s present activities and absorption remainder by British Legation;
b. Designation Caccia to act in dual role UK HICOM and Minister;
c. Reduction in British supporting as opposed to combat forces.” (763.0221/3–2050)
). Latter has not yet advised him of French reaction, merely mentioning in conversation two days ago that Madame BethouartPresumably a reference to the wife of Gen. Emile Béthouart, French High Commissioner and Commander in Chief for Austria. had gotten wind of plan and in thought French
may take similar action, is now busily engaged in lobbying for designation her husband as joint French Minister-High Commissioner.
